A similar size to an industrial oven, the machine is intended for business use and will cost around £25,000 ($38,000). 

The machine allows landlords to brew their own beer for a quarter of the price of buying it in from a brewery. 

The British Beer & Pub Association refused to comment on how much it typically costs larger breweries to brew a pint 'for competition reasons.' 

But Dave Bailey, the founder of Hardknott Brewery in Cumbria told The Guardian in 2011 that it cost 90p to make a pint of beer, including 3p for malt, 2p for hops, 20p for labour and 20p for duty and 12p for transport.

