Inventor Mr McLauchlan, 67, from Stratford-upon-Avon, Warkwickshire, said: ‘Craft ale is the story of the moment and major brands are being shunned by consumers who now seek interesting and really good beers with local provenance.

‘Pubs can benefit enormously from this by brewing their own beer and that’s where Truebrew comes in.’ 

Landlords can create unique beers to attract customers.

‘And because they brew the beer onsite, pubs can guarantee it is fresh and there is no need for chemicals or preservatives or other additives that the public have no idea about,’ Mr McLauchlan said.

The machine has just gone on general sale in the UK and will launch in the US in 'the next couple of months'. 

